National Assembly Speaker Baleka Mbete and National Council of Provinces Chairperson Thandi Modise will join many South Africans at the house of late ANC stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela today, to pay their respects. Madikizela-Mandela died on Monday at the Netcare Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg after a long illness. On Monday, both presiding officers expressed shock and collective grief over the passing of Madikizela-Mandela, who was also popularly known as the “Mother of the Nation”. “Ms Madikizela-Mandela was a founding member of the democratic Parliament of South Africa in 1994,” both leaders said in a statement on Tuesday. -TNA Reporter